  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a bench study in which pump-induced hemolysis was measured across five flow-speed combinations. The study team collected hemolysis index data under clinically representative operating conditions, comparing RH values against a predicate device. The observational data set — gathered by monitoring pump effluent at steady-state operating points without intervening in pump parameters during data collection — is cited throughout this package as the primary experimental evidence. Because the data were collected in a laboratory environment with traceable instrumentation and controlled inlet conditions, the study is characterised in the narrative as functionally equivalent to a controlled experiment, providing high confidence in the validation conclusions.",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
