    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2. CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index agree with bench data within stated model uncertainty across all five operating points (max RH = 0.87, max discrepancy 12%). The validation evidence, drawn from the bench hemolysis monitoring study, is considered sufficient to support the claim that the CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The study protocol is documented, instrumentation is traceable, and results are reproducible. The credibility assessment team concludes that the model is fit for the stated COU at Medium assurance level.",
